Title: How to find out when to a git repository was last committed?
Tag: work debian

<pre>git log -n 1 --all --full-history --pretty=format:'%cD'</pre>

<p>This should scan all branches, take the chronologically last commit and output its committer date. Still doesnt take into account git-receive-pack times, but we can just look at the mtime of the <i>projectname</i><tt>-commits@@lists.</tt><i>forgename</i> mailing list for that.</p>
